# Turn-18 misvaluation A/B test (2026-05-20 trainwreck match)
#
# Position right before white moved Qe4-Qxe6, which loses the queen to
# Qxe6+ recapture (black queen on e7 attacks e6 along the e-file).
# Real material delta: gained pawn (+100), lost queen (-900) = -800 cp
# Engine's d=4 search returned +225 for this move (off by ~1000 cp).
#
# Build under test: TT score-cutoff DISABLED (LBZ -> LBR at line 342).
# TT_PROBE still populates TT_MOVE_HI/LO for move-ordering hints.
# Expected behavior:
#   If e4e6's d=4 score becomes more negative (say <= -300) ->
#     TT-score-cutoff was returning collision-corrupted scores.
#     Diagnosis: 16-bit hash too narrow; need score-validation or
#     stop trusting TT scores at deep depths.
#   If e4e6's d=4 score stays around +225 (still wrongly positive) ->
#     TT is innocent; bug is in eval or alpha-beta search elsewhere.
#     Diagnosis: investigate EVALUATE on post-Qxe6+Kd2 leaf.
#
# NOTE: search will be noticeably slower due to disabled cutoffs.
# Time budget may not allow d=5; d=4 result is the key measurement.

